quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  6,42,"Ere this We sent unto nations before you, and We sent them distress and adversity that per chance (or possibly) they might humble themselves"
  6,43,"If only, when Our violence falls upon them, they had been humble, but their heart was hard, and Satan made seemly to them all that they used to do"
  6,44,"And when they forgot what they were reminded of, We opened for them the gates of all things, until when they rejoiced at what they had, We caught them up suddenly (or unawares, unexpectedly), and Lo! They were plunged into despair"
  6,45,"And the uttermost part of the people who did wrong were cut off. Praise be to Allah, Lord of the worlds"
  6,46,"Say, \"Think you! If Allah should remove your hearing and your sight, and should set a seal upon your heart, who is god but Allah to restore it to you?\" See how We expound the revelations unto them! Yet still they turn away"
  6,47,"Say, \"Think! If Allah´s punishment should come to you unawares or openly (expectedly), would any perish save the people who do wrong"
  6,48,"We do not send our messengers save as heralds of glad tidings and of warning, and whoever believes and acts aright, there is no fear for them, and they shall not be grieved"
  6,49,"But those who deny Our signs, torment shall afflict them, because they used to disobey"
  6,50,"Say (O Muhammad), \"I do not say unto you that mine are the treasuries of Allah, nor that I know the unseen, and I do not say unto you, I am an angel. I follow only that which is inspired in me.\" Say, \"Is the blind man equal to him who sees"